						<summary>

						<p>Stone (No. 2) lying near the P.W.D. Office.</p>						

						<p>1703 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record registers a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> to Śarabhayya, son of Rāghappayya by Ja[mnagiri] Bāva, the <hi rend="italic">guru</hi> of Hindurāya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1625, Subhānu, Vaiśākha śu. 12, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1703 A.D., April, 16, Friday, f.d.t. ·65.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
